cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the problem of accurately localizing an object with respect to a robot, which is a key step in autonomous robotic manipulation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper proposes a method that relies on a classification Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) trained using hundreds of thousands of synthetically rendered scenes with randomized parameters. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions that the approach does not require calibration of the cameras, which could indicate that it belongs to the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. Finally, the paper involves building a new dataset of real robot images, which could suggest that it belongs to the category cs.GR (Graphics).
